Prodorsum ( Figs. 7 ,
10– 13
). Rostrum divided by deep median incision. Rostral setae smooth, 13 in length, arched inwards. The costulae long, parallel, widened at their median parts and reaching to the median incision of the rostrum. Lamellar setae 5 in length, arising at the distal end of the costulae, situated closer to rostral setae than to interlamellar setae. Interlamellar setae minute, 2 in length and arising in anterior one-third of the interbothridial protuberance. Lamellar and interlamellar setae smooth. Bothridia well developed. Sensilla with long stalk and little dilated, strongly barbed elliptical heads.

Legs (
Figs. 14–17
). All legs monodactylous. Setation of leg segments is given in figures 14–17 .
